Package: consort-session-bin
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         dbus-x11,
         gsettings-desktop-schemas,
         upower (>= 0.9.0)
Conflicts: consort-session (<< 2.26.1-5)
Description: Consort Session Manager - Minimal runtime
 The Consort Session Manager is in charge of starting the core components
 of the GNOME desktop, and applications that should be launched at
 login time. It also features a way to save and restore currently
 running applications.
 .
 This package contains the binaries for the Consort Session Manager, but
 no startup scripts. It is meant for those willing to start
 consort-session by hand with the components of their choice, and for
 applications such as GDM that use consort-session internally.

